# Suggested QA checklist for AADB

You can implement this as a pre-export validator.

## Connector QA
- [ ] every directed edge has arrowhead
- [ ] no arrowhead clipped by node or container
- [ ] no connector crosses a label
- [ ] no connector overlaps unrelated node
- [ ] max 2 elbows preferred
- [ ] parallel lines separated by minimum lane distance

## Bubble QA
- [ ] no bubble overlaps node/icon/text
- [ ] no bubble within 18 px of elbow
- [ ] no bubble within 18 px of arrowhead
- [ ] no bubble on container border
- [ ] bubble center lies on straight segment
- [ ] bubble labels match legend numbering

## Label QA
- [ ] no truncation unless approved abbreviation
- [ ] labels fully readable at export size
- [ ] icon/name vertical spacing is sufficient
- [ ] line labels do not overlap connectors/bubbles

## Container QA
- [ ] nodes maintain min padding from container borders
- [ ] container titles unobstructed
- [ ] inner group boxes not overcrowded

## Composition QA
- [ ] major flows readable left-to-right
- [ ] hub nodes have extra whitespace
- [ ] no visually dense hotspot without rerouting
- [ ] diagram remains readable at 100% zoom and presentation scale

